  "Description": "The Start goal initiates a series of tests to verify the behavior of asynchronous and synchronous goal calls. It begins by logging the start of the tests, then proceeds to execute three distinct tests: the first test checks that the main execution continues immediately after calling an asynchronous goal without waiting; the second test verifies that a synchronous call waits for completion; and the third test confirms that the asynchronous goal has completed its execution by checking the contents of a file. The goal also includes error handling for missing files and assertion failures, ensuring robust testing of the asynchronous functionality.",
